cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper proposes a method for template matching in unconstrained environments, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The paper focuses on addressing the challenges of scaling and rotation, which are key issues in this area. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper introduces a novel similarity measure and uses statistical analysis to justify its properties, which suggests that it could also fit into the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also includes experiments on both synthetic and real-world data, which could place it in the categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.RO (Robotics).
